    {
      "id": "l8-days",
      "type": "theory",
      "title": "Time words",
      "body": "# Days and periods\n\nWords for when things happen:\n\n- **Today** (आज) · **Tomorrow** (कल, आने वाला) · **Yesterday** (कल, बीता हुआ)\n- **Day** (दिन) · **Week** (सप्ताह) · **Month** (महीना) · **Year** (साल)\n\nNote that Hindi uses **कल** for both *tomorrow* and *yesterday*, but English has **two different words**. Watch the context: *I will come tomorrow* (future) vs *I came yesterday* (past)."
    },
    {
      "id": "l8-ex-match-days",
      "type": "exercise",
      "title": "Match the time words",
      "exercise": {
        "id": "l8-ex-match-days",
        "type": "matching",
        "prompt": "Match each English time word with its Hindi meaning.",
        "card_ids": [
          "hi-today",
          "hi-tomorrow",
          "hi-yesterday",
          "hi-week"
        ],
        "pairs": [
          {
            "left": "Today",
            "right": "आज"
          },
          {
            "left": "Tomorrow",
            "right": "कल (आने वाला)"
          },
          {
            "left": "Yesterday",
            "right": "कल (बीता हुआ)"
          },
          {
            "left": "Week",
            "right": "सप्ताह"
